      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(ui): rename chat sessions from the picker",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\nFixes an issue where users would break their chat workflow to rename a session. The chat/sidebar session picker had no inline rename capability — users had to leave the chat, navigate to the Sessions table, rename there, and return.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\nInline rename on the picker itself keeps users in their chat context. The implementation reuses the existing `sessions.patch` label contract rather than introducing a new API. Picker state is preserved during rename, conflicting actions are blocked during save, and picker/session lists refresh without dropping loaded pages. The rename-triggered refresh is tied to the picker's request-generation counter so a newer search arriving during the refresh flight is not overwritten — including the duplicate-signature path (see hardening note below). Scope is the Control UI session picker only.\n\n## User Impact\nUsers can double-click a session name in the chat picker/sidebar to rename it inline, without leaving their conversation. Session rename is available directly where sessions are selected.\n\n## Evidence\n\n**Vitest:**\n```\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs ui/src/ui/views/chat.test.ts --run\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  124 passed (124)\n```\n\n**Concurrency hardening — duplicate-signature rename refresh (addresses the [P1] race finding):**\n\n`refreshChatSessionPickerAfterRename` previously dropped the generation guard when the refresh signature matched an already-active search (`beginChatSessionPickerSearchRequest` returned `null`): the post-`await` assignment then ran unguarded, so a newer search dispatched while the rename `sessions.list` was in flight could be overwritten by the stale refresh. The branch now invalidates the duplicate and re-acquires a live generation, so the post-`await` `isCurrentChatSessionPickerSearchRequest` check always runs and a newer search wins. This removes the unsafe special-case (net `+14/-14`, one canonical guarded path).\n\nHonest coverage note: the full `chat.test.ts` suite (124 tests, incl. the existing rename-refresh race test) stays green, confirming no regression. I was not able to construct a *deterministic* DOM-level reproduction of the duplicate-signature timing that fails on the pre-fix code, so I did not add a test that passes against the unfixed branch (a green-on-buggy test would be false assurance). The hardening is a strict superset of the prior guarding and matches the picker's existing request-generation contract.\n\n**Browser proof:**\n\n![picker-open](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/3d0f75e2-3ab2-4d7e-ae3f-6493127e1d8e)\n![rename-editing](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/c0baa1f5-a0d1-423f-90a1-429a49c3f440)\n![rename-saved](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/3634e733-f17c-4ac7-b92f-e693c52443de)\n![rename-reopened](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/790e8f86-55e2-483f-9d01-43ca441ca8a5)\n\n**Video:** [session-picker-rename.webm](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/5a7f19ab-f79d-4d80-8381-ff1eee2f7850)\n",
        "branch": "fix/89922-session-picker-rename",
